Is this intentionally mutating the `Session` object?
If not:


```suggestion
function Session.new()
  local state = {
    bufnr = vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf(),
    tabstops = {},
    current_tabstop = Tabstop.new(0, self.bufnr, { 0, 0, 0, 0 })
  }
  return setmetatable(state, __index = Session)
end
```

If it is intentional, I'd tend towards using a regular global table, without class style because class style usually involves different instances with encapsulated state.

```suggestion
  return vim.split(table.concat(text), '\n', { plain = true })
```

I can see `snippet.get()` being part of a more mature version of the API that exposes relevant info for external libraries to build on top of. However I'm unsure of what details we'll be exposing.

> If so perhaps we should rename this or at least change the return type, else it will be redundant.

@justinmk I'm not fully understanding the suggestion (and the why) here.
